name: Dr. Alma Alo
about: Doctor of Medicine (abbreviated M.D., from the Latin Medicinae Doctor) is a medical degree, the meaning of which varies between different jurisdictions.

name: Dr. Connor Cancio
about: The MS in biomedical informatics at NYU School of Medicine’s Sackler Institute of Graduate Biomedical Sciences sharpens students’ practical skills in basic science, translational science, and medical research

name: Dr. Hannah Durphey
about: A master’s degree may be required for certain jobs of graduate degree programs. Students can use them to broaden their educational horizons of specific subjects or business sectors, and degrees can improve earning potential as well.

name: Dr. Danny Carmella
about: The MPH degree focuses on public health practice, as opposed to research or teaching. Master of Public Health programs are available throughout the world in Schools of Public Health

name: Dr. Tyler Peil
about: The advantages of MMed over membership certificated qualifications are that, whilst both groups are clinically competent at their levels, MMed specialist can enrol into a four year PhD plus fellowship and come out as consultants with PhD or do a two year fellowship without PhD.

name: Dr. Jose Lueckenotte
about: An MPhil typically includes a taught portion and a significant research portion, during which a thesis project is conducted under supervision.
